For a founder, Salesforce Agentforce is a signal that the market is moving from “AI as a feature” to “AI as an operating layer” inside the enterprise.

What it means for positioning:
- You can’t win by saying “we also have AI.”
- You need a sharper wedge: a specific workflow, role, or outcome Salesforce won’t own end-to-end.
- Buyers will increasingly compare you to a platform narrative, not just point tools.
- Your message should emphasize depth, speed to value, or domain specialization.
- If you overlap with CRM/workflows, frame yourself as the system that solves the last-mile problem Salesforce won’t optimize for.

What to do next:
- Re-check your ICP: are you selling to a Salesforce buyer, an adjacent buyer, or a replacement buyer?
- Rewrite positioning around a narrow job-to-be-done, not generic “AI productivity.”
- Map your product against Agentforce: integrate, complement, or compete.
- Build one crisp proof point: ROI, time saved, conversion lift, or operational risk reduced.
- Tighten your talk track so you can answer: “Why not just use Salesforce?”

Salesforce, Inc. is headquartered in San Francisco, CA, and Agentforce is part of its broader enterprise AI push. {{fact:ground_truth:SALESFORCE}}

